{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 2000128, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Crawclaw", "body": "Poor Ner'zhul. He was only trying to save his people and then he lost his soul to the voidwalkers. Shame we couldn't work with him to fight the Iron Horde.", "date": "2014-09-06T20:09:50-05:00", "rating": 21, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Considering he pretty much sold his entire clan to the Void in an attempt to get into the Iron Horde, can't say I feel the slightest amount of pity for him. He was always a bastard, regardless of timeline.", "creationdate": "2014-09-29T17:39:52-05:00", "id": 775758, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2000128, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Elyseon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If the Shadowmoon were good as well it would have undercut the special snowflake spiel they're playing with the Frostwolves. Too bad. *sigh*", "creationdate": "2014-09-29T18:43:00-05:00", "id": 775774, "rating": -1, "commentid": 2000128, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LanceofAbel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "na, the original timeline Ner'Zhul is a pitiable character. Who wouldn't be deceived by the guise of the spirit of your long lost beloved wife. He couldn't cope with the shame when he later found out and the rest of his story is what most people judge him on.", "creationdate": "2014-10-02T19:25:25-05:00", "id": 776294, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2000128, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "SHO57", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "yeah, i agree with ^, i dont know what im more upset with; that Kil'Jaeden tricked him with that in the first place, or that the spirit of his own wife wouldnt forgive him. i sort of expected more from the almost omnipotent Orcish Ancestors than a simple \"oh, look, youve screwed it all up. good job, we're out.\"", "creationdate": "2014-10-03T02:10:03-05:00", "id": 776337, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2000128, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "shamanfang", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 2013389, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tovosh", "body": "His powers are a definite reference to his counterpart when he became The Lich King.", "date": "2014-10-15T10:22:36-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I wouldn't be so sure. Most of the Lich King's power is not innate but granted by the helmet.", "creationdate": "2014-10-23T03:11:41-05:00", "id": 781420, "rating": -1, "commentid": 2013389, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Enquillion", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The helmet has the soul of Ner'Zhul in it... His powers are what the Lich King is using.", "creationdate": "2014-11-09T15:23:06-06:00", "id": 787566, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2013389, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LilyValentin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ner'zhul is the Lich King, the Lich King is Ner'zhul. Its 1 and the same person. When Arthas put on the helm, then Arthas and Ner'zhul kinda merged. Arthas eventually overcame and became the dominant personality.", "creationdate": "2014-11-18T02:34:58-06:00", "id": 792338, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2013389, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Pootie", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I'm fairly certain Ner'zhul, in the current timeline, is still alive in the Lich King helmet. Why would the helmet itself still have power over a \"majority\" of the scourge if Ner'zhul, whose power the Lich King used, no longer existed? Where would the power to control the scourge come from at that point? The only conclusion is that part of Ner'zhul still exists in the helmet.", "creationdate": "2015-01-28T00:07:46-06:00", "id": 833440, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2013389, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LilyValentin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 2020423, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kaerfemagsh", "body": "if we kill this guy in this dungeon, then how can he become the 1st lich king? if he's not made lich king because he's dead then how can he lead arthas to the frozen throne to become the 2nd lich king? if that doesn't happen then who the hell will the final boss of icecrown citadel be?", "date": "2014-10-28T23:22:28-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Alternate timeline bro", "creationdate": "2014-11-05T12:42:41-06:00", "id": 786237, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2020423, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "darrianl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Alternate universe. This isn't the Ner'zhul who becomes the Lich King. Blizzard's marketing department really dropped the ball on this one. They kept touting the time travel thing instead of the AU part, and wound up confusing everyone.", "creationdate": "2014-11-20T21:46:07-06:00", "id": 795196, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2020423, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "meganerd18", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If alternate arthas doesnt show up in like patch 6.3 or something then i feel that blizz dropped the ball as the alliance has had all their chars sorta made crazy or killed off by the horde they sorta need to use this timeline to reintroduce a bit more strength into the alliance to balance it withe the horde", "creationdate": "2014-12-02T19:23:43-06:00", "id": 805110, "rating": -1, "commentid": 2020423, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ragemonkey", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The hell are you talking about? There won't be an alternate Arthas, the Alliance has NOT had all their characters \"made crazy or killed off\" by the Horde, and indeed both sides lost a lot in the Fourth War. Varian is still alive, Anduin is still alive, Kurdran and Falstad are still alive, Moira is still alive, Malfurion is still alive, Velen is still alive, the Alliance has loads of characters still alive.", "creationdate": "2014-12-04T02:45:00-06:00", "id": 806093, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2020423, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "meganerd18", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 2039255, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Reignac", "body": "What matter isn't where the boss fight is held. What kind of instance they die in isn't important. What matters is what the bosses do [i]before[/i] their death, in the world and in quests, and of all the Warlords Ner'zhul is definitely the best off in that department.\n\nHe has the most appearances in questlines. The main Shadowmoon Valley storyline is about Ner'zhul and stopping him. The only Warlord who compares to that is Fenris in Frostfire Ridge, and he's not even one of [i]the[/i] Warlords and dies in a quest. All the other Warlords just show up for one quest, if they show up [i]at all[/i]--Grom and Kilrogg are totally absent between the Tanaan intro and level 100, and even at cap they barely do anything. Kargath is just an afterthought in one quest at the end of Spires. Blackhand as a badass cutscene, but he only shows up five minutes before that cutscene and then runs off again.\n\nNone of them get as much screen time as Ner'zhul, even if they die in raids.\n\nI'm happy with Ner'zhul's treatment in WoD.", "date": "2014-11-18T22:28:04-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-11-18T22:43:09-06:00", 1, "Reignac"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 2040018, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ceemeeir", "body": "In case you have problem with him on heroic, then here is a tip: he can be easily kited between his aoe splashes. You will lose your tank's damage, but healer has to heal nothing on the tank. May be valid tactic on challenge mode also with a hunter to increase DPS to 4.", "date": "2014-11-19T09:36:09-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-11-19T09:39:29-06:00", 1, "ceemeeir"]}
